name: Triple
statement: Given an array $$$a$$$ of $$$n$$$ elements, print any value that appears at least three times or print -1 if there is no such value.
inputFormat: The first line contains an integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \leq t \leq 10^4$$$) — the number of test cases. The first line of each test case contains an integer $$$n$$$ ($$$1 \leq n \leq 2\cdot10^5$$$) — the length of the array. The second line of each test case contains $$$n$$$ integers $$$a_1, a_2, \dots, a_n$$$ ($$$1 \leq a_i \leq n$$$) — the elements of the array. It is guaranteed that the sum of $$$n$$$ over all test cases does not exceed $$$2\cdot10^5$$$.
outputFormat: For each test case, print any value that appears at least three times or print -1 if there is no such value.
